11/05/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Two more ministers may be involved in the ongoing corruption scandal in Bulgaria, according to Atanas Atanasov, a Parliament member from the opposition Democrats for Strong Bulgaria.
Atanasov identified them on Thursday (May 10th) as Regional Development Minister Asen Gagauzov and Deputy Prime Minister Emel Etem from the Movement for Rights and Freedoms, who is on leave until the elections for European Parliament.
The corruption scandal has already resulted in the dismissal of two deputy ministers and the suspension of Deputy Prime Minister Rumen Ovcharov.
(Sega, Dnevnik, Trud - 11/05/07;
bTV - 10/05/07)
